.IX Title "pEFL::Elm::Icon 3pm"
.TH pEFL::Elm::Icon 3pm 2022-11-01 "perl v5.38.2" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.\" For nroff, turn off justification.  Always turn off hyphenation; it makes
.\" way too many mistakes in technical documents.
.if n .ad l
.nh
.SH NAME
pEFL::Elm:Icon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 5
\&  use pEFL::Elm;
\&  [...]
\&  my $widget = pEFL::Elm::Icon\->add($parent);
\&  my $theme = $widget\->theme_get();
\&  [...]
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module is a perl binding to the Elementary Icon widget.
.PP
For more informations see https://www.enlightenment.org/develop/legacy/api/c/start#group_\|_Elm_\|_Icon.html
.PP
For instructions, how to use pEFL::Elm::Icon, please study this API reference for now. A perl-specific documentation will perhaps come in later versions. But applying the C documentation should be no problem. pEFL::Elm::Icon gives you a nice object-oriented interface that is kept close to the C API. Please note, that the perl method names remove the "elm_icon_" at the beginning of the c functions.
.SS EXPORT
.IX Subsection "EXPORT"
None by default.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
https://www.enlightenment.org/develop/legacy/api/c/start#group_\|_Elm_\|_Icon.html
